---
name: explain-code
description: Explains code clearly and practically. Use when explaining how code works, specific parts of a codebase, or when the user asks "how does this work?"
input:
  code: The code snippet to explain
  focus: Optional – specify what part or concept to focus on (e.g. "async logic", "this function", "error handling", "performance")
---

When explaining code, always:

1. Explain WHAT the code does
   - High-level summary first
   - Then break into logical parts

2. Explain HOW it works
   - Step-by-step flow
   - Mention important constructs (loops, async, closures, etc.)

3. Explain WHY it is written this way
   - What problem it solves
   - Why this approach might have been chosen

4. Call out important details
   - Hidden complexity
   - Side effects
   - Edge cases

5. Highlight a gotcha
   - Common mistakes or misunderstandings
   - Things that might break or confuse developers

6. Suggest alternatives and best practices
   - Cleaner / modern approaches
   - Performance or readability improvements
   - When you would choose a different pattern

Guidelines:
- Be conversational, not academic
- Use real-world analogies only if helpful
- Do NOT use diagrams
- Focus on practical understanding for developers
- If "focus" is provided, prioritize that area but still give brief context